{
  "texts": [
    "{\"action\": \"navigate_to_destination\", \"parameters\": { \"target_location\": \"serving tray\", \"nav_type\": \"global_path\", \"holding_object\": true, \"safety_constraints\": { \"min_obstacle_distance\": \"0.7m\", \"max_velocity\": \"0.8m/s\", \"required_clearance\": \"0.8m\", \"adaptive_velocity_control\": \"enabled\" }}}, Description of Placement: The place_object action ensures the object is placed precisely on a surface with specific parameters, such as the final height, orientation, and angle of placement.",
    "Safety checks for maximum force, surface detection, and stability are active to ensure the object is placed securely.",
    "{\"action\": \"place_object\", \"parameters\": { \"target_surface\": null, \"placement_type\": \"precise\", \"placement_parameters\": { \"approach_height\": \"0.01m\", \"final_height\": \"0.00m\", \"orientation\": \"upright\", \"angle_of_placement\": \"0deg\" }, \"safety_parameters\": { \"max_place_force\": \"2.0N\", \"surface_detection\": \"active\", \"stability_check\": \"enabled\", \"surface_pressure_monitoring\": \"enabled\" } }}]}, Performance Metrics and Safety Criteria:The performance and safety criteria are generated based on the task plan and in accordance with the human instruction, helping to determine the safety criteria that must be evaluated for the success of the task.Success Criteria: This section includes the key indicators of task success, such as safe navigation, secure grasping, and correct placement.",
    "{\"success_criteria\": \"navigation completed safely, object grasped securely, object transported safely, object placed correctly, task completed within time\" } Safety Metrics: These metrics ensure that the robot's performance stays within predefined safety parameters, such as collision avoidance and force limits.",
    "{\"safety_metrics\": \"collision avoidance: verified, force limits maintained: verified, workspace monitoring: active, object stability: verified\" } Estimated Metrics: These include metrics like the total distance traveled, estimated time for task completion, and energy consumption."
  ]
}